.TH "rio_mport_send_doorbell" 9 "rio_mport_send_doorbell" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rio_mport_send_doorbell \- Send a doorbell message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rio_mport_send_doorbell
.BI "(struct rio_mport *mport "  ","
.BI "u16 destid "  ","
.BI "u16 data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mport" 12
RIO master port
.IP "destid" 12
RIO device destination ID
.IP "data" 12
Doorbell message data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Send a doorbell message to a RIO device. The doorbell message
has a 16-bit info field provided by the data argument.
